sys_remote_update_set.description:
@author: github.com/derekpage3
@version 0.6 (Geneva+)
SOURCE: https://github.com/derekpage3/ServiceNow

DESCRIPTION: This update set provides a new  experimental background script editor, similar to the out of box "Scripts - Background" tool provided by ServiceNow, but with the  JavaScript editor interface.   The tool is built using a standard form so the level of functionality provided by the script editor is entirely dependent on the version of ServiceNow the tool is installed on and the Script field editor capabilities associated with it.  No customizations have been made to the Script field's implementation (TinyMCE as of this writing).

WARNING: Any scripts run from the interface will run with the permission level of the current user (security_admin if elevated, admin otherwise).  Exercise caution in the scripts you run from this interface.  All of the customary guidelines from the OOB ServiceNow background scripts page apply here.

DO NOT INSTALL THIS ON REGULAR INSTANCES, AS THIS TOOLSET MAY INTRODUCE POTENTIAL SECURITY VULNERABILITIES THAT ARE NOT ACCEPTABLE IN A REAL ENVIRONMENT WITH CUSTOMER DATA IN IT.  THIS TOOL IS ONLY INTENDED FOR USE IN A PERSONAL DEVELOPER INSTANCE WITH NO SENSITIVE DATA IN IT.
